title: Fun in Roscoe Village
text: Our teenagers loved Roscoe Village last year (and so did we!) Learn all about life long ago by watching RE-inactors in time period clothing tell the history begins their professions (Dr, Seamstress, metalworks maker, etc). Be pulled along the towpath in a boat by horses... lots of fun here!

title: Fun in Amish Country
text: This place is great for adults and kids! It’s a free petting zoo (you can buy very inexpensive cones with pellet food to feed the goats if you’d like). The best baked goods ever! Try their homemade fry pies and cream sticks but don’t go too late in the day or they’re sold out!!

title: Sonny & Stacie
text: Hundreds of desserts to choose from. Various coffees and great prices!!! Every single one was Delicious!!!

title: Stacie & Sonny
text: We went up to this city to watch the sunset but unfortunately it was very cloudy out that day. We were expecting rain so our tour guides were very accommodating and got us to see all of it destinations and we ended up eating last while it started to sprinkle which was very nice. title: Sonny & Stacie
text: We took a van tour while in Santorini and we visited the white beach, red beach and Black Beach. All were very different and very beautiful ! Great backdrop for photos !

title: Stacie & Sonny
text: We took a van tour one day while in Santorini And visited the black beach, read beach and white beach. All were beautiful and very and visited the black beach, red beach and white beach. All were beautiful and very different!

title: Stacie & Sonny
text: We took a tour in a minivan and went to the red beach, Black Beach and white beach. All beaches were beautiful and very different!

title: Stacie and Sonny
text: Great wine and view was fantastic but a bit pricey and also their chef had been sent home early unfortunately (and we were hungry!)

title: Sonny & Stacie
text: We took a donkey ride while in Santorini with Spiros. We went down to the old port where we took a boat out to the volcano and over to the Hot Springs. The donkey ride was very exciting and something we will always remember! Fun hiking in the volcanic area!

title: Sonny & Stacie
text: Greece was on our bucket list! It was so amazing! The Acropolis was stunning but go early because they’re not open too late. Architecture is beyond amazing here!

title: Stacie & Sonny
text: My Boss was here about 6 months ago and gave us Giannis’s phone number because he was so friendly and efficient. We’re so glad we called him. He was even a bit early each time to pick us up! He was even happily willing to pick us up at 4 am to take us back to the airport. We had to take a cab with someone else when we were sightseeing in Corinth and I was scared to death! That guy did not drive like Giannis!! Giannis drives the speed limit and obeys the rules :-). Giannis is very knowledgeable on the area of Athens since he’s lived here his entire life and gave ya great suggestions on where to eat, sights to see, etc. He comes highly recommended!!! Thank you Giannis for everything!

title: Canopy tour
text: Had an awesome time today. First time zip lining. Wish we would’ve had time to do the extended tour. Lots of fun and staff was super! Thank you!
